<REVIEW>
The rain hammered against the windows, each drop a tiny percussion in nature's relentless symphony. The storm had been building all afternoon, dark clouds gathering like an army on the horizon.
Lightning split the sky, illuminating the empty street below. The rain hammered against the windows, each drop a tiny percussion in nature's relentless symphony. Thunder followed seconds later, shaking the old house to its foundations.
</REVIEW>

<REPETITION ISSUES>
- MATCH: `The rain hammered against the windows, each drop a tiny percussion in nature's relentless symphony.`
</REPETITION ISSUES>

<ANALYSIS>
- Thought process: The AI has repeated an exact sentence - "The rain hammered against the windows, each drop a tiny percussion in nature's relentless symphony." Additionally, the prose is overwrought with metaphors like "nature's relentless symphony" and "army on the horizon."
- Purple prose: YES - "nature's relentless symphony," "army on the horizon"
- Over-description: MINOR - could be tighter
- Length: TOO LONG
- Tense: PAST - "The rain hammered"
- Mature content: N/A
- Repetition: YES - exact sentence repeated
</ANALYSIS>

<FIX>
Rain hammered the windows all afternoon as dark clouds rolled in. Lightning split the sky, lighting up the empty street. Thunder shook the old house seconds later.
</FIX>

