<REVIEW>
The garden stretched before her, a verdant paradise of botanical splendor. Each rose petal glistened with morning dew like diamonds scattered by some celestial jeweler. The birdsong created a mellifluous tapestry of sound that wove itself through the gossamer threads of the early morning mist.
She sat on the bench and breathed in the fresh air.
</REVIEW>

<ANALYSIS>
- Thought process: The first part is drowning in purple prose - "verdant paradise," "celestial jeweler," "mellifluous tapestry," "gossamer threads." Then the last sentence is perfect - simple and clear. The contrast shows exactly what good writing looks like versus overwrought description.
- Purple prose: SEVERE - nearly every phrase in the first part
- Over-description: YES - simple garden scene made absurdly complex
- Length: TOO LONG
- Tense: PAST - "stretched before her"
- Mature content: N/A
</ANALYSIS>

<FIX>
The garden was lush with roses still wet from the morning dew. Birds sang through the early mist.
She sat on the bench and breathed in the fresh air.
</FIX>

